  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA11-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu kāppu mikutikkaṇ iṭaiyīṭupaṭṭu āṟṟāḷāka talaimakaṭkut talaimakaṉ (G1+2, ET: talaivaṉ) ciṟaippuṟattāṉākat tōḻi colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what the confidante said while HE was behind the fence to HER who was unable to bear it when obstacles turned up in an increase of guarding.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA11">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            peyyātu vaikiya kōtai pōla</l>
<l>            meycā yiṉaiyavar ceykuṟi piḻaippa</l>
<l>            vuḷḷi notumalar nērpurai teḷḷitiṉ</l>
<l>            vārā reṉṉum pulavi yuṭkoḷa</l>
<l>            loḻika māḷaniṉ ṉeñcat tāṉē </l>
<l>            puṇari poruta pūmaṇa laṭaikarai</l>
<l>            yāḻi maruṅki ṉalava ṉōmpi</l>
<l>            valavaṉ vaḷpāyn tūra</l>
<l>            nilavu virintaṉṟāṟ kāṉa lāṉē.</l>

        </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
        <l>O you emaciated in [your] body, like a garland kept unworn,<note place="foot">Here we have two possibilities of understanding <term xml:lang="ta">peyyātu</term>, namely either as "unworn" or as "unwatered". The parallel to be found in KT 9.2f. (<term xml:lang="ta">ceppiṉ tamiya vaikiya | peyyā pūviṉ mey cāyiṉaḷē</term>) made me adopt the former possibility.</note></l>
        <l>leave off<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">oḻika</term>: the translation forces us to render an impersonal construction in the Tamil (<term xml:lang="ta">uḷ koḷal oḻika</term> "may the taking to mind stop") by a personal one as see above.</note> in your heart</l>
        <l rend="indent">from taking vexation to mind, saying:</l>
        <l rend="indent3">“he won't come,</l>
        <l rend="indent"> 
            <choice>
                <seg>for sure, [since] strangers talk of [our] meeting”,</seg>
                <seg>for sure, [since they] talk of my parents consenting to a stranger,</seg>
            </choice>
            </l>
        <l rend="indent3">remembering</l>
        <l rend="indent">how [you] failed the sign he made.</l>
        <l>Moonlight indeed has spread on the seashore,</l>
        <l rend="indent">while the charioteer checks the reins [and] moves slowly</l>
        <l rend="indent">protecting crabs on the side of the wheels</l>
        <l rend="indent2">on the shore where sand sets, flowers struck by the ocean.</l>
    </lg>
